                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Confidential.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 287.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-07-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 5,</hi> 1862.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of June 20 (No. 176) has been
                    received.</p>
                <p>It is a satisfaction to know that a copy of my despatch 260 has been received and
                    read by Earl Russell. The subject it presents is one of momentous import. It
                    seems as if the extreme advocates of African slavery and its most vehement
                    opponents were acting in concert together to precipitate a servile war—the
                    former by making the most desperate attempts to overthrow the federal Union, the
                    latter by demanding an edict of universal emancipation as a lawful and
                    necessary, if not, as they say, the only legitimate, way of saving the
                    Union.</p>
                <p>I reserve remarks upon the military situation for a day nearer to the departure
                    of the mail.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
